[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello, I was wondering whether there are any selftest or kunit tests that I could contribute to. I am also interested in driver dev.<br>\nI would really appreciate it if someone could point me towards something that I can work on.</p>",
        "id": 465945510,
        "sender_full_name": "Siddharth M",
        "timestamp": 1724920846
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I noticed that enabling  KUnit tests was unchecked <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/927\">here</a></p>",
        "id": 465946339,
        "sender_full_name": "Siddharth M",
        "timestamp": 1724921029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have doctests executed via KUnit, but support for <code>#[test]</code> was not yet upstreamed. There are patches somewhere. I would personally really like to have <code>#[test]</code> available upstream.</p>",
        "id": 465947086,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724921151
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Looking.20for.20something.20to.20work.20on.20.28Like.20tests.20or.20drivers.29/near/465947086\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>support for <code>#[test]</code> was not yet upstreamed. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What do you mean with this?</p>\n<p>We at least have (short) <a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/testing.html#the-test-tests\">The <code>#[test]</code> tests</a> documentation. And running that on v6.11-rc5 I get [1]. Whatever that tests, though <span aria-label=\"wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f609\" role=\"img\" title=\"wink\">:wink:</span></p>\n<p>[1]</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">j8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rusttest</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">CALL</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">checksyscalls</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">build_error</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">uapi</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">running</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tests</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">passed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ignored</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">measured</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">filtered</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">finished</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.00</span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTDOC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">macros</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">running</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">13</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tests</span>\n<span class=\"n\">iiiiiiiiiiii</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">passed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">12</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ignored</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">measured</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">filtered</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">finished</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.05</span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">running</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tests</span>\n<span class=\"o\">........</span>\n<span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">result</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">passed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ignored</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">measured</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">filtered</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">finished</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.00</span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 465988438,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1724931707
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that runs the test locally on your device, not inside of kunit</p>",
        "id": 465988733,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1724931783
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As Benno says. KUnit boots the kernel in a VM and runs tests there. What <code>#[test]</code> is currently doing is also useful, so perhaps we need another attribute, or an argument like <code>#[test(kunit)]</code>.</p>",
        "id": 466001931,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1724934645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for taking the time to respond, will see if there's anything I can do relating to that. </p>\n<p>I also came across a commit mentioning that KUnit does not support assertions in other tasks, so errors are simply printed to the kernel log if an assertion fails.</p>",
        "id": 466267687,
        "sender_full_name": "Siddharth M",
        "timestamp": 1725024205
    }
]